0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"x:mx-auto x:flex x:max-w-(--nextra-content-width)","children":["$","$L2",null,{"value":[{"value":"Tools","id":"tools","depth":2},{"value":"Resources","id":"resources","depth":2}],"children":[["$","$L3",null,{}],["$","$L4",null,{"metadata":{"title":"MCP (AI)","filePath":"src/content/mcp.mdx"},"sourceCode":"---\ntitle: MCP (AI)\n---\n\n# AI: the MCP server\n\n`@telekinesis/mcp` lets an LLM author timesheets against your **live** frames,\nguarded by the JSON Schema so it can't emit an unplayable sheet.\n\n```json\n{ \"mcpServers\": { \"telekinesis\": { \"command\": \"telekinesis-mcp\" } } }\n```\n\n## Tools\n\n- `extract_ui_context({ url })` — list every registered `<TelekineticFrame>` on a\n  running page (id, intent, viewport rect). Append `?demo` to force demo mode.\n- `generate_timesheet({ url | frames, goal })` — a **schema-validated** draft to\n  refine.\n\n## Resources\n\n- `telekinesis://schema/timesheet` — the full JSON Schema (refs inlined).\n- `telekinesis://effects` — the action + sound catalog.\n\nThe model reasons over real frames; the schema is the guardrail. Refine the\ndraft by hand or drop it into the [Studio](/studio) to tune it visually.","children":[["$","div",null,{"id":"nextra-skip-nav"}],["$","main",null,{"data-pagefind-body":true,"children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"x:tracking-tight x:text-slate-900 x:dark:text-slate-100 x:font-bold x:mt-2 x:text-4xl","children":["AI: the MCP server","$undefined"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":[["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"@telekinesis/mcp"}]," lets an LLM author timesheets against your ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"live"}]," frames,\nguarded by the JSON Schema so it can’t emit an unplayable sheet."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"data-pagefind-ignore":"all","className":"nextra-code x:relative x:not-first:mt-[1.25em]","children":["$undefined",["$","pre",